\section{Results}

In this section we describe our results for central galaxies, following the method outlined in Section 3. ANN pattern recognition training is performed on 50,000 SF and 50,000 PA galaxies for each configuration of science variables considered. Once the ANN model is constructed, it is tested on a new verification set of 50,000 SF and 50,000 PA galaxies. The output probability distributions, ROC curves and AUC parameters are determined for each case. From this, a ranking of how important different galaxy properties, and sets of two and three properties, are for determining the passive state of galaxies is constructed.



